fastPathRoutingIpv6.name: fastPathRoutingIpv6
fastPathRoutingIpv6.description: The Ubiquiti Private MIB for FastPath Ipv6 Routing

agentIpv6RoutingMode.name: agentIpv6RoutingMode
agentIpv6RoutingMode.description: Administratively enables/disables ipv6 unicast routing on the switch.

agentIpv6InterfaceIfIndex.name: agentIpv6InterfaceIfIndex
agentIpv6InterfaceIfIndex.description: The IfIndex associated with this instance.

agentIpv6InterfaceMtuValue.name: agentIpv6InterfaceMtuValue
agentIpv6InterfaceMtuValue.description: Configures the MTU value for this interface.If it is not yet configured, retrieving the value of this object results in a zero value. Setting the value zero to this object effectively un-configures the MTU.

agentIpv6InterfaceDadTransmits.name: agentIpv6InterfaceDadTransmits
agentIpv6InterfaceDadTransmits.description: Configures the dad transmits value for this interface.

agentIpv6InterfaceLinkLocalOnly.name: agentIpv6InterfaceLinkLocalOnly
agentIpv6InterfaceLinkLocalOnly.description: When enabled, interface is capable of ipv6 operation without a global address. In this case, an eui-64 based link-local address is used.

agentIpv6InterfaceIcmpUnreachables.name: agentIpv6InterfaceIcmpUnreachables
agentIpv6InterfaceIcmpUnreachables.description: If this object is enable, it indicates that ICMPv6 unreachables can be sent on this interface.

agentIpv6InterfaceAutoconfig.name: agentIpv6InterfaceAutoconfig
agentIpv6InterfaceAutoconfig.description: If this object is enabled, it indicates that the IPv6 address is automatically generated using IPv6 stateless address auto configuration.

agentIpv6InterfaceDhcpClient.name: agentIpv6InterfaceDhcpClient
agentIpv6InterfaceDhcpClient.description: If this object is enabled, the interface uses DHCPv6 Client protocol to acquire an IPv6 address.

agentIpv6InterfaceIcmpRedirects.name: agentIpv6InterfaceIcmpRedirects
agentIpv6InterfaceIcmpRedirects.description: Enable/Disable the sending of ICMPv6 redirect messages in the redirect scenario where the forwarded packet is sent out through the same interface on which the packet was received.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementTable.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementTable
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementTable.description: There is no global administrative flag for router advertisement. The global routing flag (agentIpv6RoutingMode) will be used for this purpose. If routing is disabled, router advertisement is disabled as well.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementIfIndex.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementIfIndex
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementIfIndex.description: Interface Number to configure Router Advertisement on.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementSuppressMode.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementSuppressMode
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementSuppressMode.description: Enable or disable router advertisement suppression on the interface.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementMaxAdvertise.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementMaxAdvertisementInterval
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementMaxAdvertise.description: Maximum time allowed between sending router advertisements from the interface.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementAdvertisemen.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementAdvertisementLifetime
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementAdvertisemen.description: Value of lifetime field of router advertisement sent from the interface. This value must be greater than or equal to agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementMaxAdvertisementInterval.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementNbrSolicitIn.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementNbrSolicitInterval
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementNbrSolicitIn.description: Value of retrans time field of router advertisement sent from the interface. A value of 0 means this router does not specifiy the interval.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementReachableTim.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementReachableTime
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementReachableTim.description: Value of reachable time field of router advertisement sent from the interface. A value of 0 means this router does not specifiy the interval.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementManagedFlag.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementManagedFlag
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementManagedFlag.description: Value of managed config field of router advertisement sent from the interface.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementOtherFlag.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementOtherFlag
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementOtherFlag.description: Value of other config field of router advertisement sent from the interface.

agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementHopLimitUnsp.name: agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementHopLimitUnspecifiedMode
agentIpv6RouterAdvertisementHopLimitUnsp.description: This object configures the router to send Router Advertisements on an interface with unspecified (0) Current Hop Limit value. This will tell the hosts on that link to ignore the Hop Limit from this Router.

agentIpv6AddrPrefixTable.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixTable
agentIpv6AddrPrefixTable.description: The list of IPv6 address prefixes of IPv6 interfaces.

agentIpv6AddrPrefixEntry.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixEntry
agentIpv6AddrPrefixEntry.description: An interface entry containing objects of a particular IPv6 address prefix.

agentIpv6AddrPrefix.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefix
agentIpv6AddrPrefix.description: The prefix associated with the this interface.

agentIpv6AddrPrefixLength.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixLength
agentIpv6AddrPrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix (in bits).

agentIpv6AddrPrefixOnLinkFlag.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixOnLinkFlag
agentIpv6AddrPrefixOnLinkFlag.description: This object has the value 'true(1)', if this prefix can be used for on-link determination and the value 'false(2)' otherwise.

agentIpv6AddrPrefixAutonomousFlag.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixAutonomousFlag
agentIpv6AddrPrefixAutonomousFlag.description: Autonomous address configuration flag. When true(1), indicates that this prefix can be used for autonomous address configuration (i.e. can be used to form a local interface address). If false(2), it is not used to autoconfigure a local interface address.

agentIpv6AddrPrefixAdvPreferredLifetime.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixAdvPreferredLifetime
agentIpv6AddrPrefixAdvPreferredLifetime.description: It is the length of time in seconds that this prefix will remain preferred, i.e. time until deprecation. A value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity. The address generated from a deprecated prefix should no longer be used as a source address in new communications, but packets received on such an interface are processed as expected.

agentIpv6AddrPrefixAdvValidLifetime.name: agentIpv6AddrPrefixAdvValidLifetime
agentIpv6AddrPrefixAdvValidLifetime.description: It is the length of time in seconds that this prefix will remain valid, i.e. time until invalidation. A value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity. The address generated from an invalidated prefix should not appear as the destination or source address of a packet.

agentIpv6AddrTable.name: agentIpv6AddrTable
agentIpv6AddrTable.description: The table of addressing information relevant to this node's interface addresses.

agentIpv6AddrEntry.name: agentIpv6AddrEntry
agentIpv6AddrEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this node's interface addresses.

agentIpv6AddrAddress.name: agentIpv6AddrAddress
agentIpv6AddrAddress.description: The IPv6 address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

agentIpv6AddrPfxLength.name: agentIpv6AddrPfxLength
agentIpv6AddrPfxLength.description: The length of the prefix (in bits) associated with the IPv6 address of this entry.

agentIpv6AddrEui64Flag.name: agentIpv6AddrEui64Flag
agentIpv6AddrEui64Flag.description: This object has the value 'true(1)', if this address uses and eui-64 generated interface identifier and the value 'false(2)' otherwise.

agentIpv6AddrStatus.name: agentIpv6AddrStatus
agentIpv6AddrStatus.description: Creates a new entry in the Address table. Allowed values are: createAndGo(4) - Creates an entry in this table, associating the address with a given interface. The agentIpv6NetMask object must be set during creation. destroy(6) - Removes the associated address from the interface.

agentIpv6StaticRouteTable.name: agentIpv6StaticRouteTable
agentIpv6StaticRouteTable.description: IPv6 Static Routing table. This table contains an entry for each valid IPv6 static unicast route that can be used for packet forwarding determination.

agentIpv6StaticRouteDest.name: agentIpv6StaticRouteDest
agentIpv6StaticRouteDest.description: The destination IPv6 address of this route. This object may not take a Multicast address value.

agentIpv6StaticRoutePfxLength.name: agentIpv6StaticRoutePfxLength
agentIpv6StaticRoutePfxLength.description: Indicates the prefix length of the destination address.

agentIpv6StaticRouteIfIndex.name: agentIpv6StaticRouteIfIndex
agentIpv6StaticRouteIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ipv6IfIndex. For routes with global address next hop this value can be zero.

agentIpv6StaticRouteNextHop.name: agentIpv6StaticRouteNextHop
agentIpv6StaticRouteNextHop.description: The address of the next system en route.

agentIpv6StaticRoutePreference.name: agentIpv6StaticRoutePreference
agentIpv6StaticRoutePreference.description: The routing preference metric for this route. A lower value is more preferred.

agentIpv6StaticRouteStatus.name: agentIpv6StaticRouteStatus
agentIpv6StaticRouteStatus.description: Creates a new entry in the Address table. Allowed values are: createAndGo(4) - Creates an entry in this table. destroy(6) - Removes the associated route from the interface.

agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixTable.name: agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixTable
agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixTable.description: IPv6 Service Port Prefix Table. This table contains an entry for each valid IPv6 prefix configured on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixEntry.name: agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixEntry
agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixEntry.description: An IPv6 Service Port Prefix entry.

agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixIndex.name: agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixIndex
agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixIndex.description: The index of the Ipv6 Prefix Address configured on the Service Port. Removal of a row will cause index values to be reassigned.

agentIpv6ServicePortPrefix.name: agentIpv6ServicePortPrefix
agentIpv6ServicePortPrefix.description: The Ipv6 Prefix Address configured on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixLength.name: agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixLength
agentIpv6ServicePortPrefixLength.description: The length of the IPv6 Prefix Address.

agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterTable.name: agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterTable
agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterTable.description: IPv6 Service Port Default Router Table. This table contains an entry for each valid IPv6 Default Router configured on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterEntry.name: agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterEntry
agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterEntry.description: An IPv6 Service Port Default Router entry.

agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterIndex.name: agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterIndex
agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouterIndex.description: The index of the IPv6 Default Router Address configured on the Service Port. Removal of a row will cause index values to be reassigned.

agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouter.name: agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouter
agentIpv6ServicePortDefaultRouter.description: The Address of the IPv6 Default Router configured on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrTable.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrTable
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrTable.description: IPv6 Service Port Neighbor Table. This table contains an entry for each valid IPv6 Neighbor configured on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrEntry.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrEntry
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrEntry.description: An IPv6 Service Port Neighbor entry.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrAddr.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrAddr
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrAddr.description: The Ipv6 Address of a neighbor switch visible to the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrPhysAddr.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrPhysAddr
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrPhysAddr.description: The MacAddress of the neighboring switch.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrState.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrState
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrState.description: The state of the neighboring switch: reachable(1) - The neighbor is reachable by this switch. stale(2) - Information about the neighbor is scheduled for deletion. delay(3) - No information has been received from neighbor during delay period. probe(4) - Switch is attempting to probe for this neighbor. unknown(6) - Unknown status.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrUpdated.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrUpdated
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrUpdated.description: The last sysUpTime that this neighbor has been updated.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrIsRouter.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrIsRouter
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrIsRouter.description: Returns true(1) if the neighbor machine is a router, false(2) otherwise.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrType.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrType
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrType.description: The type of the mapping. The 'dynamic(2)' type indicates that the IPv6 address to physical addresses mapping has been dynamically resolved using the IPv6 Neighbor Discovery protocol. The static(3)' types indicates that the mapping has been statically configured. The local(4) indicates that the mapping is provided for an entity's own interface address.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgTable.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgTable
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgTable.description: The table contains an entry for each static IPv6 Neighbor on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgEntry.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgEntry
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgEntry.description: An entry of the static IPv6 Neighbor on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgAddr.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgAddr
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgAddr.description: The Ipv6 Address of a static neighbor on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgPhysAddr.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgPhysAddr
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgPhysAddr.description: The MAC Address of a static neighbor on the Service Port.

agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgEntryStatus.name: agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgEntryStatus
agentIpv6ServicePortNbrCfgEntryStatus.description: Create or delete the static neighbor entry on the Service Port. The configured static neighbor entry is always active.

agentIpv6IcmpRateLimitInterval.name: agentIpv6IcmpRateLimitInterval
agentIpv6IcmpRateLimitInterval.description: Specifies the time interval between tokens being placed in the bucket for ICMP Ratelimit.

agentIpv6IcmpRateLimitBurstSize.name: agentIpv6IcmpRateLimitBurstSize
agentIpv6IcmpRateLimitBurstSize.description: Specifies the number of tokens to be placed after timeout.

agentDhcp6ClientParametersTable.name: agentDhcp6ClientParametersTable
agentDhcp6ClientParametersTable.description: Information about the DHCPv6 Client parameters on the interfaces.

agentDhcp6ClientParametersEntry.name: agentDhcp6ClientParametersEntry
agentDhcp6ClientParametersEntry.description: DHCPv6 Client information on an interface.

agentDhcp6ClientInterfaceIndex.name: agentDhcp6ClientInterfaceIndex
agentDhcp6ClientInterfaceIndex.description: The Interface index on which the IPv6 address is leased by the DHCPv6 Server.

agentDhcp6ClientPrefix.name: agentDhcp6ClientPrefix
agentDhcp6ClientPrefix.description: The IPv6 Prefix leased by the DHCPv6 Server.

agentDhcp6ClientPrefixlength.name: agentDhcp6ClientPrefixlength
agentDhcp6ClientPrefixlength.description: The Prefix length corresponding to the IPv6 Prefix leased by the DHCPv6 Server.

agentDhcp6ClientState.name: agentDhcp6ClientState
agentDhcp6ClientState.description: The State of the DHCPv6 Client on this interface.

agentDhcp6ClientServerDUID.name: agentDhcp6ClientServerDUID
agentDhcp6ClientServerDUID.description: The DHCPv6 Unique Identifier of the DHCPv6 Server on this interface.

agentDhcp6ClientT1Time.name: agentDhcp6ClientT1Time
agentDhcp6ClientT1Time.description: The T1 (in seconds) time as indicated by the DHCPv6 Server. T1 value indicates the time interval after which the address is requested for renewal.

agentDhcp6ClientT2Time.name: agentDhcp6ClientT2Time
agentDhcp6ClientT2Time.description: The T2 (in seconds) time as indicated by the DHCPv6 Server. T2 value indicates the time interval after which the Client sends Rebind message to the Server incase there are no replies to the Renew messages.

agentDhcp6ClientIAID.name: agentDhcp6ClientIAID
agentDhcp6ClientIAID.description: An identifier for an identity association chosen by this Client.

agentDhcp6ClientPreferredLifeTime.name: agentDhcp6ClientPreferredLifeTime
agentDhcp6ClientPreferredLifeTime.description: The time (in seconds) that the IPv6 address is leased by the DHCPv6 Server.

agentDhcp6ClientValidLifeTime.name: agentDhcp6ClientValidLifeTime
agentDhcp6ClientValidLifeTime.description: The time (in seconds) that the IPv6 address is leased by the DHCPv6 Server.

agentDhcp6ClientRenewTime.name: agentDhcp6ClientRenewTime
agentDhcp6ClientRenewTime.description: The time (in seconds) remaining to send a DHCPv6 Renew request to DHCPv6 Server for the leased address.

agentDhcp6ClientExpireTime.name: agentDhcp6ClientExpireTime
agentDhcp6ClientExpireTime.description: The time (in seconds) when the DHCPv6 leased address expires.

agentIpv6ConnectedRoutes.name: agentIpv6ConnectedRoutes
agentIpv6ConnectedRoutes.description: The number of connected routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6StaticRoutes.name: agentIpv6StaticRoutes
agentIpv6StaticRoutes.description: The number of static routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv66to4Routes.name: agentIpv66to4Routes
agentIpv66to4Routes.description: The number of 6to4 routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6OspfRoutes.name: agentIpv6OspfRoutes
agentIpv6OspfRoutes.description: The number of OSPFv2 routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6OspfIntraRoutes.name: agentIpv6OspfIntraRoutes
agentIpv6OspfIntraRoutes.description: The number of OSPFv2 intra-area routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6OspfInterRoutes.name: agentIpv6OspfInterRoutes
agentIpv6OspfInterRoutes.description: The number of OSPFv2 inter-area routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6OspfExt1Routes.name: agentIpv6OspfExt1Routes
agentIpv6OspfExt1Routes.description: The number of OSPFv2 external type 1 routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6OspfExt2Routes.name: agentIpv6OspfExt2Routes
agentIpv6OspfExt2Routes.description: The number of OSPFv2 external type 2 routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6BgpRoutes.name: agentIpv6BgpRoutes
agentIpv6BgpRoutes.description: The number of BGP routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6EbgpRoutes.name: agentIpv6EbgpRoutes
agentIpv6EbgpRoutes.description: The number of external BGP routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6IbgpRoutes.name: agentIpv6IbgpRoutes
agentIpv6IbgpRoutes.description: The number of internal BGP routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6LocalBgpRoutes.name: agentIpv6LocalBgpRoutes
agentIpv6LocalBgpRoutes.description: The number of local BGP routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6RejectRoutes.name: agentIpv6RejectRoutes
agentIpv6RejectRoutes.description: The number of reject routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6TotalRoutes.name: agentIpv6TotalRoutes
agentIpv6TotalRoutes.description: The number of routes in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6BestRoutes.name: agentIpv6BestRoutes
agentIpv6BestRoutes.description: The number of IPv6 routes in the forwarding table.

agentIpv6BestRoutesHigh.name: agentIpv6BestRoutesHigh
agentIpv6BestRoutesHigh.description: The highest number of IPv6 routes in the forwarding table.

agentIpv6AlternateRoutes.name: agentIpv6AlternateRoutes
agentIpv6AlternateRoutes.description: The number of alternate routes in the IPv6 routing table. An alternate route is less preferred than the best route and is not used for forwarding.

agentIpv6RouteAdds.name: agentIpv6RouteAdds
agentIpv6RouteAdds.description: The number of routes added to the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6RouteModifies.name: agentIpv6RouteModifies
agentIpv6RouteModifies.description: The number of routes changed in the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6RouteDeletes.name: agentIpv6RouteDeletes
agentIpv6RouteDeletes.description: The number of routes removed from the IPv6 routing table.

agentIpv6UnresolvedRouteAdds.name: agentIpv6UnresolvedRouteAdds
agentIpv6UnresolvedRouteAdds.description: The number of IPv6 route adds that failed because none of the route's next hops were on a local subnet.

agentIpv6InvalidRouteAdds.name: agentIpv6InvalidRouteAdds
agentIpv6InvalidRouteAdds.description: The number of IPv6 routes adds that failed because the route was invalid.

agentIpv6FailedRouteAdds.name: agentIpv6FailedRouteAdds
agentIpv6FailedRouteAdds.description: The number of IPv6 routes adds that failed because of a resource limitation in the routing table

agentIpv6ReservedLocals.name: agentIpv6ReservedLocals
agentIpv6ReservedLocals.description: The number of IPv6 routing table entries reserved for a local subnet on a routing interface that is down.

agentIpv6UniqueNextHops.name: agentIpv6UniqueNextHops
agentIpv6UniqueNextHops.description: The number of distinct next hops used among all IPv6 routes currently in the routing table. These include local interfaces for local routes and neighbors for indirect routes.

agentIpv6UniqueNextHopsHigh.name: agentIpv6UniqueNextHopsHigh
agentIpv6UniqueNextHopsHigh.description: The highest count of unique next hops since counters were last cleared.

agentIpv6NextHopGroups.name: agentIpv6NextHopGroups
agentIpv6NextHopGroups.description: The current number of next hop groups in use by one or more routes. Each next hop group includes one or more next hops.

agentIpv6NextHopGroupsHigh.name: agentIpv6NextHopGroupsHigh
agentIpv6NextHopGroupsHigh.description: The highest count of next hop groups since counters were last cleared.

agentIpv6EcmpGroups.name: agentIpv6EcmpGroups
agentIpv6EcmpGroups.description: The number of next hop groups with multiple next hops.

agentIpv6EcmpGroupsHigh.name: agentIpv6EcmpGroupsHigh
agentIpv6EcmpGroupsHigh.description: The high water mark of the number of ECMP groups.

agentIpv6EcmpRoutes.name: agentIpv6EcmpRoutes
agentIpv6EcmpRoutes.description: The current number of IPv6 routes with multiple next hops.

agentIpv6TruncEcmpRoutes.name: agentIpv6TruncEcmpRoutes
agentIpv6TruncEcmpRoutes.description: The number of ECMP routes that are currently installed in the forwarding table with just one next hop. The forwarding table may limit the number of ECMP routes or the number of ECMP groups. When an ECMP route cannot be installed because such a limit is reached, the route is installed with a single next hop.

agentIpv6EcmpRetries.name: agentIpv6EcmpRetries
agentIpv6EcmpRetries.description: The number of ECMP routes that have been installed in the forwarding table after initially being installed with a single next hop.

agentIpv6EcmpCountTable.name: agentIpv6EcmpCountTable
agentIpv6EcmpCountTable.description: A count of the number of routes with each number of ECMP next hops. A walk of this table only returns the entries with a non-zero value for agentIpv6EcmpRouteCount.

agentIpv6EcmpCountEntry.name: agentIpv6EcmpCountEntry
agentIpv6EcmpCountEntry.description: Number of IPv6 routes with a given number of next hops.

agentIpv6EcmpNextHopCount.name: agentIpv6EcmpNextHopCount
agentIpv6EcmpNextHopCount.description: The number of next hops in a route. From 0 to the maximum number of next hops in an ECMP route. The maximum varies by platform.

agentIpv6EcmpRouteCount.name: agentIpv6EcmpRouteCount
agentIpv6EcmpRouteCount.description: The number of IPv6 routes with agentIpv6EcmpNextHopCount next hops.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrTable.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrTable
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrTable.description: IPv6 Network Port Neighbor Table. This table contains an entry for each valid IPv6 Neighbor configured on the Network Port.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrEntry.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrEntry
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrEntry.description: An IPv6 Network Port Neighbor entry.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrAddr.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrAddr
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrAddr.description: The Ipv6 Address of a neighbor switch visible to the Network Port.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrPhysAddr.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrPhysAddr
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrPhysAddr.description: The MacAddress of the neighboring switch.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrState.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrState
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrState.description: The state of the neighboring switch: reachable(1) - The neighbor is reachable by this switch. stale(2) - Information about the neighbor is scheduled for deletion. delay(3) - No information has been received from neighbor during delay period. probe(4) - Switch is attempting to probe for this neighbor. unknown(6) - Unknown status.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrUpdated.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrUpdated
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrUpdated.description: The last sysUpTime that this neighbor has been updated.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrIsRouter.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrIsRouter
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrIsRouter.description: Returns true(1) if the neighbor machine is a router, false(2) otherwise.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrType.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrType
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrType.description: The type of the mapping. The 'dynamic(2)' type indicates that the IPv6 address to physical addresses mapping has been dynamically resolved using the IPv6 Neighbor Discovery protocol. The static(3)' types indicates that the mapping has been statically configured. The local(4) indicates that the mapping is provided for an entity's own interface address.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgTable.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgTable
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgTable.description: The table contains an entry for each static IPv6 Neighbor on the Network Port.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgEntry.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgEntry
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgEntry.description: An entry of the static IPv6 Neighbor on the Network Port.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgAddr.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgAddr
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgAddr.description: The Ipv6 Address of a static neighbor on the Network Port.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgPhysAddr.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgPhysAddr
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgPhysAddr.description: The MAC Address of a static neighbor on the Network Port.

agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgEntryStatus.name: agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgEntryStatus
agentIpv6NetworkPortNbrCfgEntryStatus.description: Create or delete the static neighbor entry on the Network Port. The configured static neighbor entry is always active.

agentIpv6NbrCfgTable.name: agentIpv6NbrCfgTable
agentIpv6NbrCfgTable.description: The table contains an entry for each static IPv6 Neighbor on the Network Port.

agentIpv6NbrCfgEntry.name: agentIpv6NbrCfgEntry
agentIpv6NbrCfgEntry.description: An entry of the static IPv6 Neighbor on the Network Port.

agentIpv6IfIndex.name: agentIpv6IfIndex
agentIpv6IfIndex.description: A unique non-zero value identifying the particular IPv6 interface.

agentIpv6NbrCfgAddr.name: agentIpv6NbrCfgAddr
agentIpv6NbrCfgAddr.description: The Ipv6 Address of a static neighbor on the Routing or Host interface.

agentIpv6NbrCfgPhysAddr.name: agentIpv6NbrCfgPhysAddr
agentIpv6NbrCfgPhysAddr.description: The MAC Address of a static neighbor on the Routing or Host interface.

agentIpv6NbrCfgEntryStatus.name: agentIpv6NbrCfgEntryStatus
agentIpv6NbrCfgEntryStatus.description: Create or delete the static neighbor entry on the Routing or Host interface. The configured static neighbor entry is always active.

agentIpv6NeighborsDynamicRenew.name: agentIpv6NeighborsDynamicRenew
agentIpv6NeighborsDynamicRenew.description: Enables/disables the periodic NUD (neighbor unreachability detection) to be run on the existing IPv6 neighbor entries based on the activity of the entries in the hardware. If the setting is disabled, only those entries that are actively used in the hardware are triggered for NUD. If the setting is enabled, all the entries are triggered for NUD irrespective of their usage in the hardware.

agentIpv6UnresolvedDataRateLimit.name: agentIpv6UnresolvedDataRateLimit
agentIpv6UnresolvedDataRateLimit.description: The rate in packets-per-second for the number of IPv6 data packets trapped to CPU when the packet fails to be forwarded in the hardware due to unresolved hardware address of the destined IPv6 node.

agentIpv6NUDMaxUnicastSolicits.name: agentIpv6NUDMaxUnicastSolicits
agentIpv6NUDMaxUnicastSolicits.description: The maximum number of unicast Neighbor Solicitations sent during neighbor resolution or during NUD (neighbor unreachabililty detection) before switching to multicast Neighbor Solicitations.

agentIpv6NUDMaxMulticastSolicits.name: agentIpv6NUDMaxMulticastSolicits
agentIpv6NUDMaxMulticastSolicits.description: The maximum number of multicast Neighbor Solicitations sent during neighbor resolution or during NUD (neighbor unreachabililty detection).

agentIpv6NUDBackoffMultiple.name: agentIpv6NUDBackoffMultiple
agentIpv6NUDBackoffMultiple.description: The exponential backoff multiple to be used in the calculation of the next timeout value for Neighbor Solicitation transmission during NUD (neighbor unreachabililty detection) following the exponential backoff algorithm. The next timeout value is limited to a maximum value of 60 seconds if the value with exponential backoff calculation is greater than 60 seconds.
